author: R. M. Macphail
notes: ISO 639-3: sat Santali is the most well-known Munda (non-Mon-Khmer Austro-Asiatic) language spoken in northeastern India.Source: Macphail, R. M. An Introduction to Santali. Calcutta: Firma KLM, 1983.Source: Campbell, Alexander. 1984 (reprint). A Santali-English Dictionary. 3 parts. Pokhuria: Santal Mission Press.
problems: The apostrophes in c', k', p', and t' were originally placed on top of the letters. Tildes were also always placed on top of the letters.
classification: Austro-Asiatic, Munda, North Munda, Kherwari, Santali
